{
  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who embezzled a relatively modest sum and has demonstrated remorse through partial restitution. While embezzlement is a serious breach of fiduciary duty, a decade-long sentence as suggested by the spectator is disproportionate to the offense and statutory guidelines for this amount. Considering the lack of criminal history and the mitigating factor of partial repayment, a short period of incarceration is sufficient to serve as a deterrent and punishment.",
  "verdict": 8
}
